         <abstract>
            <p>Gauss quadrature rules for evaluating integrals of the form 2π&lt;sup&gt;-1/2&lt;/sup&gt; ∫&lt;sup&gt;∞&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;0&lt;/sub&gt; exp (-x&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;)f(x)dx have been calculated to 20S for one to twenty nodes. The coefficients for the three-term recurrence relation of the first twenty orthogonal polynomials associated with the weight function exp (-x&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;) on the interval [ 0, ∞) are also tabulated to 20S.</p>
          </abstract>
